                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Catalogue no. 9; Nelson collection no. N263.  The scribe Esminis was responsible for many other price of oil receipts from Thebes between years 30 and 38 of Ptolemy II.  (See additional OIM ostraca.)  1/2 silver [kite] 1/2 obol or 1 1/2 obols is the price of 3/4 kotule or 0.20 liter of oil.  1/2 obol is the price of 1/4 kotule or 0.07 liter of oil.  Thus, a total of 2 obols were paid for a total of 1 kotule or 0.27 liter of oil.</note>
                     <note type="general">Location: Oriental Institute</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Published: recto</note>
                     <note type="lines">On recto: 4 lines in Demotic</note>
                     <note type="paleography">The writing of the season name in line 3 is clearly peret because the curved third sign is the complementary r group.  The shorter writing of the season name in line 4 must therefore be shemw, which also gives a logical sequence of dates.  In line 4, the top of the sn sign appears to be ligatured to the t sign (for sn.t, "sister").</note>
                     <note type="recto_verso">Source of description: On recto: receipt</note>
